# Section: Second Day\hfill{}$\geqq$01.06
# Genesis 01:06
God said,
{
  Let there be an expanse in the middle of the waters,
  and let it divide the waters from the waters.
}

# Genesis 01:07
God made the expanse,
and divided the waters which were under the expanse
from the waters which were above the expanse;
and it was so.

# Genesis 01:08
God called the expanse Sky.

There was evening and there was morning,
a second day.

# Section: Third Day\hfill{}$\geqq$01.09
# Genesis 01:09
God said,
{
  Let the waters under the sky be gathered together to one place,
  and let the dry land appear;
}

and it was so.

# Genesis 01:10
God called the dry land Earth,
and the gathering together of the waters he called Seas.

God saw that it was good.

# PresentationSection: Third Day\hfill{}$\geqq$01.11
# Genesis 01:11
God said,
{
  Let the earth yield grass,
  herbs yielding seeds,
  and fruit trees bearing fruit
    after their kind,
  with their seeds in it,
  on the earth;
}

and it was so.

# PresentationSection: Third Day\hfill{}$\geqq$01.12
# Genesis 01:12
The earth yielded grass,
herbs yielding seed
  after their kind,
and trees bearing fruit,
with their seeds in it,
  after their kind;
and God saw that it was good.

# Genesis 01:13
There was evening and there was morning,
a third day.

